README
======

The `count-deps` executable is used in the test-suite to detect when
the number of dependencies of certain modules change (see [this blog
post](https://blog.shaynefletcher.org/2020/10/ghc-lib-parser-module-count.html)
for motivation).

More generally it is useful for obtaining insight into a modules's
dependency graph. As used in the tests it produces (1) a count of a
module's dependencies together with the list of depended upon modules
or. However it can also (2), print a modules' dependency graph in a
fashion suitable for rendering with graphviz. See [the graphviz
downloads page](https://graphviz.org/download/) for information on
installing graphviz on your system.

Usage examples:

  (1) `inplace/bin/count-deps `inplace/bin/ghc-stage2 --print-libdir` "GHC.Parser"`
  (2) `inplace/bin/count-deps `inplace/bin/ghc-stage2 --print-libdir` "GHC.Parser" --dot`

To render a graph obtained using (2):

  - Copy the output to a file ('deps.dot' say);
  - Render the dot file ('deps.dot' from the preceding step) with a
    command like
   ```bash
   tred deps.dot > deps-tred.dot && dot -Tpdf -o deps.pdf deps-tred.dot`
   ```
